{"id": "347771", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=347771", "title": "Wulon, the Granite Sentinel", "text": "Objectives.\nKill Wulon, the Granite Sentinel.\nDescription.\nOne of the &lt;a href=\"quilen\"&gt;quilen&lt;/a&gt; statues in &lt;a href=\"Guo-Lai%20Halls\"&gt;Guo-Lai Halls&lt;/a&gt; came to life and nearly killed my precious . I won't have it! No one threatens my Kun.\nI want you to go in their and smash the thing to pieces. I'd do it myself, but I need to attend to my lover's wounds first.\nRewards.\nYou will receive: &lt;a href=\"Treasures%20of%20the%20Vale%20%28old%29\"&gt;Treasures of the Vale (old)&lt;/a&gt; and \nProgress.\nKun's doing okay. Have you smashed that statue for me yet?\nNotes.\nHead in to the &lt;a href=\"Guo-Lai%20Halls\"&gt;Guo-Lai Halls&lt;/a&gt;, down the ramp, then take a right into the &lt;a href=\"Guo-Lai%20Ritual%20Chamber\"&gt;Guo-Lai Ritual Chamber&lt;/a&gt;. Wulon is up on the raised platform. A level 90 &lt;a href=\"quilen\"&gt;quilen&lt;/a&gt; with 1,969,705 health, it has the following abilities:\nWulon cannot initially be targeted, so prepare to fight down on the lower level before approaching the steps. When ready to begin, run up the steps close to the statue, then immediately turn around and start kiting. At 90% health, the sentinel will choose one of the three fractional forms and shift into it, remaining in that form until being reduced to half health. Red Granite simply hits harder, Blue Granite drops void zones on the ground, and Green Granite does something else. Keep kiting around the platform through a second form, then finish it off. Use the knockbacks to help gain ground if Wulon catches up, especially while not in the red form, as it doesn't hit all that hard."}
