{"id": "31527", "revid": "40372170", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31527", "title": "Wushoolay", "text": "Wushoolay is a boss of the version of &lt;a href=\"Zul%27Gurub%20%28instance%29\"&gt;Zul'Gurub&lt;/a&gt;. He can still be found at the Edge of Madness, but he now has to be summoned by a skilled &lt;a href=\"Archaeology\"&gt;archaeologist&lt;/a&gt;. He is one of four available bosses there.\nBackground.\nAdventure Guide.\n\"Among the hateful spirits in the Cache of Madness are Gri'lek, a Dire troll stripped of his regenerative abilities by the loa; Renataki, an infamous and sadistic warrior; Hazza'rah, a seer tormented by dire future visions; and Wushoolay, a mighty combatant bristling with the powers of the storms.\"\nStrategy.\nOnce the summoning ritual is complete, Wushoolay may spawn and will attack the closest player. The tank should pick him up immediately and face him away from the rest of the group to limit the Forked Lightning damage.\nWushoolay will occasionally summon a Lightning Cloud on a random player. All players should get away from this cloud as soon as possible as it does massive damage.\nWushoolay will also casting Lightning Rush occasionally, where he will turn into a ball of lightning and charge a random player. Once he charges them, he will begin casting Lightning Rod which will kill anyone standing next to him at the time. Players simply need to run away from him after his Lightning Rush.\nOverall, it's a very simple fight and as long as people pay attention to their surroundings, it should be no problem for anyone.\nLoot.\nEach of the four bosses summoned drop two items: they drop one of their exclusive drops and one of their shared drops."}
