{"id": "571329", "revid": "4351312", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=571329", "title": "Wyll", "text": ""}
{"id": "334844", "revid": "210711", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=334844", "title": "Wyll Benton", "text": "Wyll Benton was an elderly servant of &lt;a href=\"Anduin%20Wrynn\"&gt;Anduin Wrynn&lt;/a&gt;. He had been taking care of Anduin since the king was little and refusing his service would offend him. As far as the king of Stormwind knew, Wyll had no family and was in service to the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Wrynn\"&gt;Wrynn&lt;/a&gt; family almost his entire life, having served King &lt;a href=\"Llane%20Wrynn%20I\"&gt;Llane&lt;/a&gt; and King &lt;a href=\"Varian%20Wrynn\"&gt;Varian&lt;/a&gt; when they, too, were young. Though old and gray-haired, Wyll was tall and heavyset. Even though he was sarcastic, Anduin knew he was a kind man, and his mild, slightly detached demeanor disguised a stubborn will and fierce devotion to the house of Wrynn. Wyll accompanied Anduin in &lt;a href=\"Ironforge\"&gt;Ironforge&lt;/a&gt; during the tumultuous events preceding the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt; but died of old age shortly after the &lt;a href=\"Argus%20Campaign\"&gt;Argus Campaign&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAs a young man, Wyll met and married a kitchen servant named &lt;a href=\"Vellcinda%20Benton\"&gt;Elsie&lt;/a&gt;, and they remained happily together for many years. Their social circles revolved around the royal families and the servants, as they themselves were.\nElsie was in &lt;a href=\"Capital%20City\"&gt;Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;, visiting family in the castle, when &lt;a href=\"Arthas%20Menethil\"&gt;Arthas&lt;/a&gt; killed &lt;a href=\"Terenas%20Menethil%20II\"&gt;King Terenas Menethil II&lt;/a&gt;. By this time, Elsie described herself as \"not young\". She was slain and raised into &lt;a href=\"undeath\"&gt;undeath&lt;/a&gt;, and later became &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; in the service of &lt;a href=\"Sylvanas%20Windrunner\"&gt;Sylvanas Windrunner&lt;/a&gt;, but Wyll assumed that she was simply killed during the city's destruction. Anduin never heard of him speak of his family in passing or in person, and suspected it was too painful for him to recall those times and what he believed to be Elsie's fate.\nThe Shattering.\nShortly before the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, Wyll accompanied his prince to &lt;a href=\"Ironforge\"&gt;Ironforge&lt;/a&gt;. After the petrification of King &lt;a href=\"Magni%20Bronzebeard\"&gt;Magni Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt;, his daughter &lt;a href=\"Moira%20Thaurissan\"&gt;Moira&lt;/a&gt; returned to Ironforge. Wyll was sent to find Anduin and &lt;a href=\"High%20Priest%20Rohan\"&gt;High Priest Rohan&lt;/a&gt; in Ironforge and tell them to see the princess. While Moira held Anduin and everyone else in Ironforge captive, Wyll told the prince that he was certain Varian was working on a liberation.\nBefore the Storm.\nWyll continued to serve as Anduin's manservant in the aftermath of the &lt;a href=\"Argus%20Campaign\"&gt;Argus Campaign&lt;/a&gt;. By this point, increasing age began preventing Wyll from performing many of his duties, but he still wanted to feel like he was useful. After Anduin's speech at &lt;a href=\"Lion%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Lion's Rest&lt;/a&gt; and the meeting with several Alliance members, Wyll tended to Anduin and spoke about their previous visit to Ironforge, as they were set to travel there again in the near future. Wyll assured Anduin that he would accompany him during his journey. Once they returned from Ironforge to Stormwind, Wyll tried to get everything ready for the next part of Anduin's journey. However, the king convinced him to stay in Stormwind instead and get a well-deserved rest.\nDays later, his health worsened, and &lt;a href=\"High%20Priestess%20Laurena\"&gt;High Priestess Laurena&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Genn%20Greymane\"&gt;Genn Greymane&lt;/a&gt; confirmed he was dying. Upon hearing this, Anduin wanted to heal the old man and restore his health, but Wyll, lying in bed in his chamber, refused. He told Anduin that he was tired of living in old age and wanted to see his deceased loved ones once again. He also stated that he had made a list of men he could recommend to serve as Anduin's new valet since the king was now a grown man and didn't need a child's servant anymore. Wyll did, however, allow Anduin to use the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; to ease his pain. Anduin remained by his side and started reading his book about the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aspects\"&gt;Dragon Aspects&lt;/a&gt; until the old man fell asleep. When he awoke, he started hallucinating about the dead loved ones waiting for him but was confused to find that Elsie was not among them. As Anduin calmed him, Wyll's last words were for Anduin to tell Elsie that he would be waiting for her. With that, the servant passed away. Anduin remained for the next hour, alone, to grieve in private.\nSpeculation.\nAs he had served both Llane and Varian when they were young, this suggests he was likely present during the &lt;a href=\"First%20War%23The%20second%20siege%20of%20Stormwind%20Keep%20and%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20kingdom\"&gt;second siege of Stormwind&lt;/a&gt; and survived the evacuation to Lordaeron."}
