{"id": "339096", "revid": "39381941", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=339096", "title": "Scorpion (Warcraft I)", "text": "Creatures of the arid lands, these giant arachnids strike with venomed stingers that are located in their tails to kill their prey. The poison they employ is extremely painful, and is a slow and wicked death. They are hunters by nature that will attack anything that strays near their nests.\nHunters of the underground, these are as venomous and deadly as any creation of the &lt;a href=\"Warlock%20%28Warcraft%20I%29\"&gt;Warlocks&lt;/a&gt;. Their tails are tipped by a sharp spike, and can tear through the armor and flesh of their prey to inject a deadly and painful poison into the unfortunate. The &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt;s have learned to command the smallest of these fiends, and can summon them to do their bidding.\nInformation.\nScorpions can be summoned by &lt;a href=\"Conjurer%20%28Warcraft%20I%29\"&gt;Conjurer&lt;/a&gt;s. They are expendable fighting units best used for scouting; pretty weak and useless in open combat. They can also serve as cannon fodder for &lt;a href=\"Catapult%20%28WC1%20Orc%29\"&gt;Catapult&lt;/a&gt;s, while distracting the Catapults, rear in some units and dispose of the Catapults. Scorpions can also be used to mob enemy &lt;a href=\"Warlock%20%28Warcraft%20I%29\"&gt;Warlocks&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necrolyte%20%28Warcraft%20I%29\"&gt;Necrolytes&lt;/a&gt;, or to harass &lt;a href=\"Peon%20%28Warcraft%20I%29\"&gt;Peons&lt;/a&gt;.\nScorpions can also be found as dungeon monsters. A lone Scorpion is encountered in the campaign mission &lt;a href=\"Northshire%20Abbey%20%28WC1%20Orc%29\"&gt;Northshire Abbey&lt;/a&gt;, and others are present in some dungeon maps.\nScorpions have a \"Magic\" bar that will slowly decay as time passes. When it is emptied, the Scorpion will continuously lose HP until it dies. Note that any Scorpions that are present at the start of a dungeon mission are not subject to decay."}
