{"id": "184435", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=184435", "title": "Revive", "text": "Revive is a &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt; ability that allows druid] to &lt;a href=\"resurrect\"&gt;resurrect&lt;/a&gt; fallen allies. It is the druid's &lt;a href=\"resurrection%20ability\"&gt;resurrection ability&lt;/a&gt;, equivalent to the shaman's &lt;a href=\"Ancestral%20Spirit\"&gt;Ancestral Spirit&lt;/a&gt; or the priest's &lt;a href=\"Resurrection\"&gt;Resurrection&lt;/a&gt;. In contrast to the &lt;a href=\"Rebirth\"&gt;Rebirth&lt;/a&gt; ability, Revive has no &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; and is only usable out of combat. \nTips.\nFor tips on resurrecting players, see &lt;a href=\"Resurrection%20ability\"&gt;Resurrection ability&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "351313", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=351313", "title": "Revive Battle Pets", "text": "Revive Battle Pets is an ability that heals a player's &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Pet\"&gt;Battle Pet&lt;/a&gt;s to full health, and resurrects any pets that are dead. It is gained through learning &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Pet%20Training\"&gt;Battle Pet Training&lt;/a&gt;. Unusually, the cooldown for this ability does not elapse when the character is logged out.\nTo heal pets without waiting for the cooldown, a player can speak to a &lt;a href=\"Stable%20Master\"&gt;Stable Master&lt;/a&gt; and pay , or use a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Pet%20Bandage\"&gt;Battle Pet Bandage&lt;/a&gt;."}
