{"id": "555397", "revid": "2043842", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=555397", "title": "Rexxar (Warcraft III)", "text": "Rexxar is the main character of the campaign &lt;a href=\"The%20Founding%20of%20Durotar\"&gt;The Founding of Durotar&lt;/a&gt;. Throughout the story of the campaign, various heroes and units can or will temporarily join him to help out in the quests he is given. &lt;a href=\"Rokhan%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Rokhan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chen%20Stormstout%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Chen&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Cairne%20Bloodhoof%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Cairne&lt;/a&gt; are three permanent additions to his party. Their levels are capped at fifteen instead of ten and they have the attribute ability which gives up to +12 for all stats at level four. If certain optional quests are completed, all the heroes with the exception of Cairne will be able to max out all five of their abilities.\nDifferences to the Base Hero Beastmaster.\n- Unique to the Founding of Durotar, Rexxar also possesses a ground to air ranged attack unlike the regular Beastmaster. He will throw axes against aerial units for the same base damage as his ground based attack. Therefore in the early game, he does not require an additional orb to attack aerial targets.\n- &lt;a href=\"Misha%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Misha&lt;/a&gt;, unlike the bear summons from regular beastmaster, is a stronger, permanent version of the summon with no set duration. Summoning Misha again will replace the existing unit on the field.\n- Rexxar also carries the &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Bolt\"&gt;Storm Bolt&lt;/a&gt; active spell instead of the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk&lt;/a&gt; Summon, giving him the ability to stun key targets while dealing significant damage."}
{"id": "423426", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=423426", "title": "Rexxar (alternate universe)", "text": "Rexxar is a &lt;a href=\"half-ogre\"&gt;half-ogre&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-orc\"&gt;half-orc&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"beastmaster\"&gt;beastmaster&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Gorgrond\"&gt;Gorgrond&lt;/a&gt; and . He is almost always seen with his dread raven companion, &lt;a href=\"Nisha%20%28dread%20raven%29\"&gt;Nisha&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nIn Gorgrond, Rexxar first appeared in &lt;a href=\"Sulfur%20Basin\"&gt;Sulfur Basin&lt;/a&gt; to fight the Iron Horde. He and &lt;a href=\"Nisha%20%28dread%20raven%29\"&gt;Nisha&lt;/a&gt; were divided and the orcs captured the raven. An adventurer tried to release Nisha from her chains, but was caught by a gronn and subsequently saved by Rexxar, who jumped on the gronn and killed it swiftly. After thanking the adventurer for saving Nisha's life, Rexxar started tending to Nisha's wounds and returned with her to his camp.\nAt the camp, Rexxar caught a nearby &lt;a href=\"Bony%20Xuk\"&gt;Laughing Skull orc&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Rangari%20Erdanii\"&gt;draenei&lt;/a&gt; out of distrust of strangers. After the adventurer vouched for the orc/draenei, Rexxar continued with his plans to eliminate the Iron Horde threat. After Nisha was fully healed, he assisted the adventurer in discovering the Iron Horde and goren's true cause of attacks, finding artifacts that could subjugate magnaron. Eventually, Rexxar, the adventurer, and the orc/draenei stopped the Iron Horde threat by killing &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Brak\"&gt;Captain Brak&lt;/a&gt; and taking &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Magnaron\"&gt;Heart of the Magnaron&lt;/a&gt;. Rexxar and Nisha are ultimately seen helping or &lt;a href=\"Yrel\"&gt;Yrel&lt;/a&gt; against and &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Gar\"&gt;Commander Gar&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Approach\"&gt;Iron Approach&lt;/a&gt;. Rexxar can also be seen in &lt;a href=\"Highpass\"&gt;Highpass&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Beastwatch\"&gt;Beastwatch&lt;/a&gt;, admiring the commander's combat, calling them a friend.\nLater, he assists the heroes in a series of quests beginning with , where he fights against the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Horde\"&gt;Iron Horde&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Blackfuse%20Company\"&gt;Blackfuse Company&lt;/a&gt; and eventually releases a rylak matriarch.\nRexxar's companions.\nAs his title of &lt;a href=\"beastmaster\"&gt;beastmaster&lt;/a&gt; suggests, Rexxar is a master of the wild and has befriended many creatures in his travels. He has been known to call upon his animal friends when needed, such as:\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nYou have proven that you have the strength to survive even the most dangerous of situations. Your technique in combat is unlike anyone I have seen. I am glad to call you friend."}
