{"id": "48368", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48368", "title": "Insignia of the Horde", "text": "Insignia of the Horde is a &lt;a href=\"quality\"&gt;quality&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"PvP%20trinket\"&gt;PvP trinket&lt;/a&gt; that removes all movement impairing effects but does not prevent them from being reapplied. Usable even if the effect would normally prevent trinket use.\nSource.\nThis item is a quest reward from &lt;a href=\"Hellfire%20Fortifications%20%28Horde%29\"&gt;Hellfire Fortifications (Horde)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt appears to not be rewarded to players who already have an equivalent Insignia trinket.\nUpgrade.\nThere is an upgraded version, the &lt;a href=\"Medallion%20of%20the%20Horde%20%28rare%29\"&gt;Medallion of the Horde (rare)&lt;/a&gt;, which is available at level 70, has only a 2-minute cooldown, and has a &lt;a href=\"Resilience\"&gt;Resilience&lt;/a&gt; bonus."}
{"id": "166278", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=166278", "title": "Insignia of the Horde (Druid)", "text": "Insignia of the Horde is a &lt;a href=\"quality\"&gt;quality&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; reward that removes all movement impairing effects but does not prevent them from being reapplied. Usable even if the effect would normally prevent trinket use. This item is popular for level 19 &lt;a href=\"twink\"&gt;twink&lt;/a&gt;s for use in &lt;a href=\"Warsong%20Gulch\"&gt;Warsong Gulch&lt;/a&gt;, where being able to break &lt;a href=\"root\"&gt;root&lt;/a&gt;ing can bring a victory.\nSource.\nThis &lt;a href=\"PvP%20rewards\"&gt;PvP reward&lt;/a&gt; item can be purchased from in the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Legends\"&gt;Hall of Legends&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orgrimmar\"&gt;Orgrimmar&lt;/a&gt; for .\nNotes.\nThe old druid insignia only removed charm, fear, and stun."}
