{"id": "758956", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=758956", "title": "Inspiration (Classic)", "text": "Inspiration is a Tier 3 &lt;a href=\"Priest%20talents%23Holy\"&gt;Holy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"talent\"&gt;talent&lt;/a&gt;. It causes criticals from almost all of your healing spells to grant a temporary physical damage reduction buff. \nNotes.\nAlthough the vast majority of priest healing spells will trigger Inspiration, certain spells will not. These include:\nInspiration does not stack with the restoration shaman's third tier talent &lt;a href=\"Ancestral%20Healing\"&gt;Ancestral Healing&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough Inspiration can proc from any of the listed spells, as the effect is of a fixed nature (not proportional to the spell's effect) and does not stack, spells that affect multiple targets (such as &lt;a href=\"Prayer%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Prayer of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Circle%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Circle of Healing&lt;/a&gt;) are far more useful for attaining this effect; even if the amount healed is small, the full effect is still granted. For Holy priests, Circle of Healing is ideal for procing Inspiration; &lt;a href=\"Penance\"&gt;Penance&lt;/a&gt; also provides an increased proc chance, with each of its 3 ticks having a chance to crit."}
